  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into<strong> </strong>fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crispy – these are your <strong>paprika fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1626718142011-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1626718142011-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1626718142011-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1626718142011-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1626718142011-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the fries are cooking, boil half a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can’t handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>to a board</p><p>Gently stir it all together – this is your <strong>spice mix</strong></p><p>Lightly splash your<strong> flat white mushrooms </strong>with <strong>water</strong>, then add to the board and turn several times until coated in the spice mix</p>",
